    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, drain your <strong>king prawns </strong>and<strong> </strong>add them to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and most of your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> (save a little for garnish!) and<strong> </strong>cook for an initial 3 min or until the prawns have started to colour</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns have started to colour, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>to the pan with 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully combined</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then stir it through the king prawns with your <strong>blanched peas</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 3-4 min or until the spinach has wilted, the sauce has thickened slightly and the prawns are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>pasta </strong>to the pan with a good grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the butter has melted and the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky garlic king prawn & pea spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-garlic-king-prawn-and-pea-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky garlic king prawn & pea spaghetti </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
